  "prompt": "What does the magnet do in blockheads?",
  "response": "In *The Blockheads*, magnets have a specific function related to mining and resource collection. Here's what they do:\n\n1. **Attract Ores and Materials**: When placed in a mining area, magnets attract certain ores and resources (like metal blocks or minerals) closer to the surface, making them easier to collect. This can save time and effort when mining.\n\n2. **Placement**: Magnets are crafted and used by placing them in the world, typically near mining spots or in tunnels where resources are being extracted.\n\nTo craft a magnet, you'll need materials like metal bars or other resources, depending on the game's crafting recipes. Magnets are especially useful for players who want to optimize their mining efforts and gather resources more efficiently.",
